  "category_subtitle": "How to tell time in Japanese",
  "category_detail": "<b>Telling Time in Japanese (時間 / じかん / jikan)</b><br><br>In Japanese, time is usually told using the counter <b>時 (じ / ji)</b> for hours and <b>分 (ふん / ぷん / fun / pun)</b> for minutes.<br><br><b>Basic Pattern</b><br>Hour + 時 (じ / ji)<br>Minute + 分 (ふん / ぷん / fun / pun)<br><br><span class=\"example\">1時</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(いちじ / ichiji)</span><br><span class=\"example\">5時</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(ごじ / goji)</span><br><span class=\"example\">10分</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(じゅっぷん / juppun)</span><br><br><b>Important Irregular Hour Readings</b><br>Some hours have special pronunciations and do not follow the normal pattern.<br><br><span class=\"example\">4時</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(よじ / yoji)</span><br><span class=\"example\">7時</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(しちじ / shichiji)</span><br><span class=\"example\">9時</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(くじ / kuji)</span><br><br><b>Important Minute Sound Changes</b><br>Minutes often change sound depending on the number.<br><br><span class=\"example\">1分</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(いっぷん / ippun)</span><br><span class=\"example\">3分</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(さんぷん / sanpun)</span><br><span class=\"example\">6分</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(ろっぷん / roppun)</span><br><span class=\"example\">8分</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(はっぷん / happun)</span><br><span class=\"example\">10分</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(じゅっぷん / juppun)</span><br><br><b>Examples</b><br><span class=\"example\">3時</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(さんじ / sanji)</span><br><span class=\"example\">7時30分</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(しちじさんじゅっぷん / shichiji sanjuppun)</span><br><span class=\"example\">9時15分</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(くじじゅうごふん / kuji juugo fun)</span><br><br><b>Useful Words</b><br><span class=\"example\">半</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(はん / han)</span> = half past<br><span class=\"example\">午前</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(ごぜん / gozen)</span> = AM<br><span class=\"example\">午後</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(ごご / gogo)</span> = PM",
